---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Capital BBQ Grill Repair | Southern California | Precision, Professional, Artisan";
const description = "$89 diagnostic waived. Capital grill repair Southern California — Precision CG-series 100k BTU U-burner, Professional PRO/PSQ, Artisan Pro 42\". Made in USA. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/capital-bbq-grill-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Capital outdoor grill lineup — Precision vs Professional vs Artisan, which do I have?",
    a: "Capital Cooking ships three active US built-in outdoor grill series. <b>Precision Series</b> is the flagship — CG-series 32\", 40\", 52\" with U-shaped 25,000 BTU stainless burners, ceramic infrared Sear Zone burner, infrared rear rotisserie burners, and integrated hidden rotisserie system; the CG52 reaches 100,000 total BTU output. <b>Professional Series</b> is the mid-premium tier — PRO32BI / PRO36BI / PRO40BI / PRO48BI / PSQ40RBIN built-in models with stainless tube burners (20,000 BTU each), W-shaped configurations on PSQ-series, electronic ignition, radiant tray heat distribution. <b>Artisan Professional Series</b> 42\" is the heritage-styled flagship with US craftsmanship emphasis. All made in the USA. Model prefix on serial plate identifies the series; Precision uses CG prefix, Professional uses PRO/PSQ, Artisan uses AP-series."
  },
  {
    q: "Precision CG-series U-burners — what's distinctive about Capital's burner architecture?",
    a: "Capital's <b>U-shaped 25,000 BTU stainless burners</b> are the Precision-series signature — same U-burner concept as Twin Eagles' Eagle One but Capital-spec sized for the CG-series chassis. Lateral flame distribution across the cooking grate (vs straight-tube H-burners on most premium grills) means more even heat edge-to-edge, fewer cold spots, better sear-zone uniformity. Service implication: Capital U-burners are proprietary to the Precision series; replacement burners ship factory-direct, $300-$460 per burner depending on size. Common failure at 7-10 year mark from outdoor exposure + thermal cycling — burner-tube corrosion, port clogging from particulate, occasional warping. We clean before recommending replacement; cleaning service $140-$220 often extends burner life another 3-5 years."
  },
  {
    q: "Ceramic infrared Sear Zone (Precision) lost temperature — tile, orifice, or regulator?",
    a: "Precision CG-series includes a dedicated infrared Sear Zone burner — ceramic emitter tile reaches 1,500°F+ for steakhouse searing. Common failures match other luxury IR burner architectures: (1) <b>Ceramic tile cracked</b> from thermal shock — cold water during cleaning or rain on hot burner; $200-$320 replacement (Capital-spec). (2) <b>Sear Zone gas orifice fouled</b> — IR orifices clog faster than main burners with particulate; cleaning service $140-$220 often resolves without parts. (3) <b>High-flow regulator drift</b> — Sear Zone needs higher gas flow than main burners; subtle drift requires flow-rate testing; $180-$280 replacement. (4) <b>Sear Zone-specific ignition</b> — separate ignition circuit from main burner ignition; if main burners light but Sear Zone doesn't, check this circuit; $200-$300 module replacement."
  },
  {
    q: "Hidden rotisserie system (Precision) — service access different from external rotisserie?",
    a: "Capital Precision's <b>hidden rotisserie system</b> conceals the spit + motor mechanism inside the grill body when not in use — pulled out for rotisserie cooking, retracted flush when grilling conventionally. Service access is more involved than external rotisserie systems on competing brands: (1) <b>Hidden rotisserie motor</b> — accessing the motor requires removing the rotisserie housing cover; $320-$480 motor replacement including extra labor. (2) <b>Spit retraction mechanism</b> — slide rails or pivot points wear at 8-12 year mark; $200-$320 service. (3) <b>Twin infrared rear rotisserie burners (Precision)</b> — two ceramic emitters above the rotisserie spit at 13,000 BTU each (26,000 BTU total); same IR-burner failure modes as Sear Zone, plus dual-burner diagnostic ($200-$320 per emitter). The hidden architecture is a Capital Precision aesthetic differentiator but adds service complexity vs externally-mounted rotisserie systems."
  },
  {
    q: "Made-in-USA Capital — LA parts chain reality?",
    a: "Capital Cooking manufactures in <b>City of Industry, California</b> — about 20 miles east of DTLA in the Inland Empire. For LA service this gives Capital a <b>2-4 day typical parts chain</b> on common service items (burners, igniters, orifices, grates, regulators), faster than Midwest/East-Coast luxury brands but not as fast as the LA-local brands (Hestan Anaheim 1-3 day, DCS via F&P Huntington Beach 1-3 day). Specialty parts and serial-matched components (Precision-specific U-burners, hidden rotisserie hardware, Artisan trim panels) may run 5-7 day factory order. Capital is a relatively small-volume luxury brand vs Twin Eagles or Lynx — parts inventory at distributor level is leaner, so the factory-direct lead time matters more for non-stock items. We set realistic expectations during diagnostic."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Capital outdoor grill repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Typical Capital bands: <b>Precision CG-series</b>: U-burner $300–$460; ceramic Sear Zone tile $200–$320; Sear Zone orifice cleaning $140–$220 (often no part); hidden rotisserie motor $320–$480; rear rotisserie IR emitter $200–$320; high-flow regulator $180–$280. <b>Professional PRO/PSQ-series</b>: stainless tube burner $260–$400; electronic ignition module $200–$320; radiant tray $140–$220; gas valve $220–$360. <b>Artisan Pro 42\"</b>: pricing similar to Precision tier with heritage-styling premium on trim parts. <b>Common to all series</b>: hot-surface igniter $160–$260; thermocouple $120–$200; control panel $380–$560; grill-grate set (stainless) $260–$400; halogen grill light $80–$140. Capital City of Industry CA factory parts chain — 2-4 day typical LA lead on common items."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Capital BBQ Grill Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$$"
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Capital BBQ Grill Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Capital outdoor grill repair across LA — Precision CG-series 32/40/52\" with U-burner + ceramic IR Sear Zone + hidden rotisserie + dual-IR rear burners; Professional PRO/PSQ-series; Artisan Professional 42\". Made in USA at City of Industry California. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Capital", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/capital/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Capital BBQ Grill Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Capital grill service?</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Capital › BBQ Grill Repair</div>
    <h1>Capital BBQ Grill Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Capital Cooking ships three active US outdoor-grill series, all made in the USA at the City of Industry California factory (~20 miles east of DTLA). <b>Precision CG-series</b> is the flagship — 32/40/52 inch built-in widths with U-shaped 25,000 BTU stainless burners, ceramic infrared Sear Zone burner, twin infrared rear rotisserie burners (26,000 BTU combined), and a hidden rotisserie system that retracts flush when not in use. CG52 reaches 100,000 total BTU output. <b>Professional Series</b> (PRO/PSQ-series 32-48 inch built-in) is the mid-premium tier with stainless tube burners and electronic ignition. <b>Artisan Professional 42 inch</b> is the heritage-styled US-craftsmanship flagship. For LA outdoor kitchens where the builder wanted real BTU output + US manufacturing without going to Twin Eagles or Kalamazoo pricing, Capital hits the $5-12k retail sweet spot. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Precision CG + Professional PRO/PSQ + Artisan Pro</b> — three-series US lineup</li>
      <li><b>Precision CG52 100k BTU</b> — U-burners + ceramic IR Sear Zone + hidden rotisserie</li>
      <li><b>City of Industry CA factory</b> — 2-4 day LA parts chain</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Capital BBQ grill repair costs in LA</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Precision U-burner</td><td>$300 – $460</td><td>Capital-proprietary, Precision-spec</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Precision Sear Zone ceramic tile</td><td>$200 – $320</td><td>Thermal shock failure</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Professional stainless tube burner</td><td>$260 – $400</td><td>PRO / PSQ-series</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Hidden rotisserie motor (Precision)</td><td>$320 – $480</td><td>Includes housing-access labor</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Rear rotisserie IR emitter (Precision)</td><td>$200 – $320</td><td>Per emitter (twin on CG-series)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Hot-surface igniter</td><td>$160 – $260</td><td>Glow-plug style</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Electronic ignition module</td><td>$200 – $320</td><td>Professional series</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas valve (per burner)</td><td>$220 – $360</td><td>Spring-fatigue diagnostic</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Grill-grate set (stainless)</td><td>$260 – $400</td><td>10+ year service</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/capital/">Capital brand hub</a> · <a href="/brands/twin-eagles-grill-repair/">Twin Eagles (US-made U-burner peer)</a> · <a href="/brands/lynx-grill-repair/">Lynx Professional</a> · <a href="/brands/hestan-outdoor-grill-repair/">Hestan outdoor (LA-local Anaheim)</a> · <a href="/brands/dcs-grill-repair/">DCS (F&P family)</a> · <a href="/brands/alfresco-grill-repair/">Alfresco (Commerce CA peer)</a> · <a href="/services/bbq-grill-repair/">BBQ grill repair (service hub)</a> · <a href="/price-list/bbq-grill-repair-cost/">BBQ grill repair cost</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Capital Precision CG52 — the 100k BTU + hidden-rotisserie spec</h2>
    <p>Capital's Precision CG52 (52-inch built-in) is the flagship spec with three 25,000 BTU U-shaped main burners + one 25,000 BTU ceramic infrared Sear Zone (100k BTU conventional cooking) + two 13,000 BTU infrared rear rotisserie burners (26k BTU rotisserie cooking) — total 126,000 BTU available across the cooking surfaces. The hidden rotisserie system is the design differentiator vs externally-mounted rotisserie on competing brands: spit + motor retract flush into the grill body when not in use, deploy out for rotisserie cooking. Service-side, the hidden architecture adds 30-45 minutes labor to rotisserie-mechanism service calls because the motor and slide rails are concealed behind a removable housing cover — tell us at booking that you have a Precision CG-series so we budget access time correctly. Hidden rotisserie aesthetic is what justifies the Capital Precision premium over Twin Eagles or Lynx in LA outdoor kitchens where the architect specified clean uninterrupted lines.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Capital BBQ grill repair — frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Capital grill service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, Ventura County. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
